# Diagnose Judge Scheduling — Runs Never Spawn

## Step

voice-call-judge is registered (worker detail + PUT sync "Successfully
registered, modified: False") yet spawns zero runs on any of its three
triggers, while sibling functions (backups, memory/run.captured) schedule
normally. 60+ voice/call.judge.requested events emitted across 2026-07-13 and
-16 produced nothing; no analyses persisted under callTelemetry custody.
Receipts: probe event accepted (ids:1) against a health-OK server with no
resulting run; GQL ConnectionRefused observed minutes earlier (server
flapping); judge opts carry `idempotency: "event.data.room"` — prime suspect:
per-room dedupe silently suppressing every re-drive, compounded by the
original 7/13 batch possibly dying in a flap window. Diagnose from the
Inngest server's own view (localhost:8288 UI/API: function state
paused/archived?, event history, skipped/dedupe counts), decide whether
idempotency-by-room is even right for a judge (re-judging a room after prompt
changes is a FEATURE — likely replace with idempotency on event id or drop
it), fix, and prove: one re-driven event → one completed run → one analysis
row readable via callTelemetry:sessionDetail. Blocks the retro build and the
A/B (both need judged receipts).

## Result (2026-07-20)

Hypothesis CONFIRMED from the Inngest server's own event history, with one
correction: scheduling was never broken. Every observation resolves to
room-keyed idempotency (24h dedupe window) plus a flapping GQL API that hid
successful runs from the CLI.

The receipts, from `eventsV2` with per-event `runs`:

- 2026-07-13: 39 judge.requested events. The first 9 (unique rooms) spawned
  runs. The 30-event re-drive the same day got NO-RUN across the board —
  per-room dedupe.
- 2026-07-16 16:33: the 30-event backfill re-drive spawned 30 COMPLETED runs
  (the 24h keys from 07-13 had expired). The CLI was flapping
  (GQL ConnectionRefused), so the session that emitted them read "zero runs"
  and chartered this step.
- 2026-07-16 17:19 + 17:23: two probe events for
  `pubcall-_+13603894321_4fbZCx3R7Ec8` — a room judged 46 minutes earlier —
  got NO-RUN. That pair next to the same room's COMPLETED run is the smoking
  gun.
- 2026-07-18 14:07: organic `voice/public-call.completed` spawned both
  voice-public-call-analyze and voice-call-judge, both COMPLETED; signed
  analysis row (mean 3.5, gpt-5.4-mini, needs-attention) readable via
  `callTelemetry:sessionDetail`. The earlier "no analyses persisted" claim was
  a reader bug: sessionDetail returns `analysis` (singular).

Fix: removed `idempotency: "event.data.room"` from voice-call-judge
(re-judging after rubric changes is a feature; each call emits exactly one
completion event; `concurrency: {limit: 2}` caps the blast radius). Host
worker respawned by worker-supervisor, re-registered.

Proof: bounded synthetic `voice/call.judge.requested` for
`pubcall-_+15052637507_QtJgHH3a6CfY` (transcript from the saved file — the
judge.requested path requires `data.transcript`; a transcript-less probe
fails fast with NonRetriableError, run 01KY0EFE62SPM16E12BCFW5YTN). Event
01KY0EJ88046NDQZBM10321MZH spawned run 01KY0EJ8CAARKPA8N651SCSWM9 for the
SAME room ~90s after the prior run — an event the old config would have
swallowed. Run COMPLETED (mean 3.71, gpt-5.4-mini, needs-attention); analysis
row createdAt 1784574252721 confirmed via `callTelemetry:sessionDetail`.
Acceptance met: one re-driven event → one completed run → one analysis row.

